				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">This isn't complicated, but just that background only allows 16x16 color definitions and doesn't allow any flipping, tiles have to be aligned on a 8x8 gird too. Using only sprites it's possible to cheat and using misaligned tiles to optimize tile usage, but that won't be possible in that case.
<br />If we don't want to store each character two times in the CHRROM, it'd be good to have the one watching in one direction always BG and the one watching in the other direction always a sprite (using horizontal flipping). 
<br />
<br />Also it'd be good to have some way of uploading the BG character in nametable in a single VBlank, maybe 2 if this simplifies things (split top/bottom, but that will introduce some minor artifacts I guess).
<br />
<br />That way, when a character jumps over another, they imediately switch the direction they're watching (as in SF2) and the BG character and sprite characters immediately get swapped.</div>

					
